Plot size considerations

Lets make a figure!

Oh no, all the labels are overlapping!! Why? The figure is only 6x4!! Theres not room for the labels :(

coffee_clean %>%
  filter(country_of_origin == "Ethiopia") %>%
  drop_na(variety) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  aes(x = variety) + 
  geom_bar()

One solution: change the size of the given chunks figure

Inside the {}, I have set figures made by THIS CHUNK ONLY to be 8x4

coffee_clean %>%
  filter(country_of_origin == "Ethiopia") %>%
  drop_na(variety) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  aes(x = variety) + 
  geom_bar()

Another solution: modify the text size itself

To do this youll need to learn more about modifying the theme here

coffee_clean %>%
  filter(country_of_origin == "Ethiopia") %>%
  drop_na(variety) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  aes(x = variety) + 
  geom_bar() + 
  # change x-axis text only - some trial and error to get the right relative size
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = rel(0.65)))

BUT!! Thats now a little too small to read, so be careful!! Maybe instead change the angle? But this is a little ugly Have to play around!

coffee_clean %>%
  filter(country_of_origin == "Ethiopia") %>%
  drop_na(variety) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  aes(x = variety) + 
  geom_bar() + 
  # rotate x-axis text 90 degrees
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))

Another solution: reconsider the plot

Maybe a horizontal plot would help

coffee_clean %>%
  filter(country_of_origin == "Ethiopia") %>%
  drop_na(variety) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  aes(y = variety) + 
  geom_bar()

What about saving the figure to a file?

Chunk figure size doesnt matter - your arguments to ggsave() matter!!

coffee_clean %>%
  filter(country_of_origin == "Ethiopia") %>%
  drop_na(variety) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  aes(x = variety) + 
  geom_bar() -> my_figure

ggsave("myfigure.png", 
       my_figure, 
       width = 8, 
       height = 4)
